<paragraph id="IFRS15_B65" base="F31717046"><paranum>B65</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 15"/><data name="paranum" value="B65"/></prolog><body><p id="IFRS15_P0752">Repurchase agreements generally come in three forms:</p><ol id="IFRS15_L0083" base="F31717048" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p id="IFRS15_P0753" base="F31717049">an entity&#x2019;s obligation to repurchase the asset (a forward);</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p id="IFRS15_P0754" base="F31717051">an entity&#x2019;s right to repurchase the asset (a call option); and</p></li><li><li_value>(c)</li_value> <p id="IFRS15_P0755" base="F31717053">an entity&#x2019;s obligation to repurchase the asset at the <xref base="F31716740" href="IFRS15_APPA.dita#IFRS15_APPA/IFRS15_P0502">customer&#x2019;s<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_customer"/></ph></xref> request (a put option).</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>